The Ondo State Police Command has confirmed an explosion at St Francis Catholic Church, Owa-luwa Street, in the Owo Local Government Area of the state. Independent had reported that an unspecified number of persons died following an explosion that occurred at the church premises. Daily Post reports that the state’s Police Public Relations Officer, PPRO, DSP Odunlami Ibukun confirmed the incident said details of the casualty would be communicated in a statement. -Advertisement- She said, “we are currently at the scene of the incident to access damages made. It is not like what have been trending on social media. We will soon issue statement to give you details of what happened.”